statement.p:
Multiply both sides of the equation
\frac{P}{1-P}=e^{t} by (1-P) and distribute on the right side to get

  P=e^{t}-Pe^{t}

Collect the terms with P on the left of

  P+Pe^{t}=e^{t}

and factor out P so that

  P(1+e^{t})=e^{t}

