statement.p:
Suppose a population is given by
P(t) = e^{t}
where t is measured in years from now. Determine when the population doubles.

Suppose a value is decaying, and \% remains after 1000 years. The amount of the substance can be modeled by the function
f(t) = Ae^{kt}
where A is the initial amount, t is the number of years, and the constant k is the continuous rate of decay. Find the value of k.

